    "verbatimText": "First line below the search box:\nGlobal / Travel / Things to Do When Your Retire / Semester Abroad\n\nKudumbashree SAS Field Program\n5 stars (28 reviews)  No Cancellation    $100 USD\nDuration\n8 hours\nCancellation\nNo refunds\nMobile Ticket\nNo tickets\nLanguage\nMalayalam, English\nOverview\nThis Semester at Sea (SAS) field program visits the Kudumbashree project in Thaneermukkom Gramapanchayath. Kudumbashree is a Kerala state government program aimed at eradicating poverty. In Malayalam, Kudumbashree means \u201cprosperity of the family,\u201d and the idea behind the program is that empowering women lifts entire families out of poverty. The field program will include an information session and an initial meeting with some of the senior women, tours of Kudumbashree projects, and lunch. Transport will be by bus.\nWhy travelers book it\n\t\u2022\tIt\u2019s an opportunity to meet local women and learn about a women\u2019s empowerment organization that you couldn\u2019t arrange on your own.\n\t\u2022\tSASers are 70% women, women\u2019s empowerment is important to them.\n\t\u2022\tIt\u2019s on the last day in Kochi, and, because it\u2019s a SAS field program, the ship will wait if the tour returns late. \n\t\u2022\tNot to miss the chance at a truly inspiring experience.\nGood to know\n\t\u2022\tThe 13,000 families of Thaneermukkom Gramapanchayath will welcome Semester at Sea.\n\t\u2022\tA man will speak for the women, but it\u2019s because he is the only one fluent in Malayalam and English.\n\t\u2022\tThe women in Kerala are better educated than the men; Kudumbashree is a way for them to use their education to benefit themselves, their families, their community, and their country.\n\t\u2022\tThe women\u2019s stories and accomplishments will inspire you.\n\nIncluded\n\t\u2022\tInformational session on history, purpose, and impact of Kudumbashree\n\t\u2022\tOpportunity to interact with women members of Kudumbashree\n\t\u2022\tTour of the Take A Break restroom and nutritional lunch factory run by Kudumbashree\n\t\u2022\tMulticourse lunch prepared and served by the women of Kudumbashree\n\t\u2022\tSinging and dancing on the bus\nNot Included\n\t\u2022\tEnough time with the women of Kudumbashree\nDetails\nMeeting Point    On board the ship at 8:00 am\nEnd Point           Outside immigration before the ship sails for Kenya\nAccessibility      No strenuous activity\nWhat to Bring    Phone camera, although the trip leader will tell you not to take photos, once the \t\t               local women start filming, you will want photos and videos of them, too\n\nReviews 5.0 (28)\nMargo W \u20145\nInspiring!\nI will never forget the woman who started her talk by saying, \u201cBefore Kudumbashree, my entire world was my kitchen,\u201d and ended by telling us that after joining Kudumbashree, she moved up through the organization\u2019s pyramid structure, then moved into national politics and was elected to the Indian Parliament\u2014for one of the open seats, not one of the seats reserved for women. Inspiring!\nPatti 5 Stars\nI\u2019ll Never Forget\nThe organization is amazing, but I will never forget the women. How we sang and danced with them on the bus, the meal they cooked for us, the many selfies taken. So glad I joined.\nJohn 5 Stars\nWhat\u2019s wrong with men?\nI don\u2019t know why no other men joined the tour. "
