    "verbatimText": "First line below the search box:\nGlobal / Travel / Things to Do When Your Retire / Semester Abroad\n\nNeptune Day on Semester at Sea\n4.8 (3,028 reviews)   No Cancellation     Free\nDuration\n6 hours\nCancellation\nNot possible to reverse head shaving\nMobile ticket\nNo\nLanguage\nEnglish\nOverview\nAs far back as the Age of Exploration, sailors have marked their first time crossing the equator with ceremony and the rituals of Neptune Day, named for the Roman god of the sea. Part initiation, part hazing, and part performance art, Neptune Day traditionally started with a royal processional led by King Neptune and his court. Pollywogs, those crossing the equator for the first time, were then initiated into the Order of Shellbacks through a series of humiliating and often dangerous rites, including the shaving of heads. Even Charles Darwin wasn\u2019t spared on the HMS Beagle. As he wrote in his diary, \u201cWe have crossed the Equator, & I have undergone the disagreeable operation of being shaved.\u201d\n\nSemester at Sea keeps this maritime tradition alive, toning down the hazing\u2014these are college students, not seasoned sailors. For hours, a procession of pollywogs moved through the same ritual: getting slimed, cleansing with saltwater, kissing the fish, kissing the ring, pledging fealty, and being declared a shellback. The final step\u2014head shaving\u2014is optional.\nWhy travelers book it\n\t\u2022\tThere is not a lot to do on a ship at sea for 10 days in the doldrums\n\t\u2022\tPeer pressure\n\t\u2022\tTo participate in an honorable nautical tradition\n\t\u2022\tAn excuse to party in a bikini\nGood to know\n\t\u2022\tThe dead fish decays as the day goes on\n\t\u2022\tClose your eyes and shut your mouth before a foaming pitcher of ice cold green slime is poured over your head.\n\t\u2022\tShikara\u2019s hit song \u201cWaka Waka (This time for Africa) is the traditional song for SAS\u2019s Neptune Day ceremonies\n\t\u2022\tIf you get your head shaved, you can choose buzz cut instead of a clean shave (bowling ball).\n\nWhat\u2019s included\n\t\u2022\tGreen slime\n\t\u2022\tSaltwater swimming pool\n\t\u2022\tDead fish\n\t\u2022\tRoyal court, including King Neptune \n\t\u2022\tTrained barber with electric shaver\n\nNot included\n\t\u2022\tBaseball cap to cover your head for the next weeks or months\n\t\u2022\tPhoto to send to your mother\n\t\u2022\tShampoo to wash out the slime\n\t\u2022\tYour dignity\n\n4.8 (3,028 reviews)   Have chat divide it\nMargo W   3 stars\nNot my thing\nI was already a shellback. I crossed the equator in the Galapagos Islands\u2014like Darwin. But if I hadn\u2019t been, I\u2019m not sure I would have joined the line. I\u2019m not that kind of joiner. Maybe I\u2019m just not that fun. Or maybe I\u2019m simply a 63-year-old retired lawyer in a rash guard, not a 20-year-old college student in a bikini.\n\nCarolyn G  5 stars\n\nTransformational\n\nMy husband Ken always loved my hair long. So, during the five years he was dying from Alzheimers, I never cut it. Keeping my hair long was something I could do for him. After Ken passed, I couldn\u2019t bring myself to change it. But planned to cut it on the ship, to shave it off on Neptune Day. When the ship crossed the equator, I did it. I shave off my long hair as part of my transformation\u2014moving forward, starting the next part of my life without Ken.\n\nJen P 5 stars\n\nParty!\n\nThe slime was cold. The fish was gross. But I\u2019m a shellback now. Great day, great party.\n\f"
