    "verbatimText": "First line below the search box:\nGlobal / Travel / Things to Do When Your Retire / Semester Abroad\n\nLes Nomades de Marrakech\n4.8 642 reviews\nDuration\nAs long as you want\nCancellation\nNo charge for entry, no refunds on purchases\nMobile ticket\nNo tickets, just walk in (if you can find it in the Medina)\nLanguage\nWhatever language the customer speaks\nOverview\nLes Nomades de Marrakech was established in 1993 by Namous Abderrahim, the fifth generation in a family renowned for its expertise in top-quality Moroccan carpets. Les Nomades unfolds a tale of heritage and craftsmanship inspired by the nomadic spirit of the region. Our rugs, especially those crafted by the Berbers in the Atlas Mountains, embody centuries of cultural exchange along ancient trade routes. Our rugs are a celebration of enduring artistry and the vibrant tapestry woven by diverse influences. Today, they travel from the villages of the Atlas Mountains to our Marrakech showroom and, finally, directly to your doorstep. \nWhy travelers shop there\n\t\u2022\tThey get lost in the Marrakech Medina and wander in.\n\t\u2022\tTheir research on buying rugs in Marrakech sends them to Les Nomades.\n\t\u2022\tTheir tour guide brings them.\n\t\u2022\tWhen you buy a Moroccan rug in Morocco, every time you see it in your home, you will smile and remember wandering lost in the Marrakech Medina and riding a camel in the Sahara. \n\nGood to know\n\t\u2022\tWalk-ins welcome, scheduling a visit ensures a tailored personal experience.\n\t\u2022\tThe tea, cookies, and lessons in history, culture, and rug weaving are free.\n\t\u2022\tNegotiate, it\u2019s expected, and can be fun if done in the right spirit.\n\t\u2022\tEvery rug tells a story.\n\t\u2022\tLes Nomades has over 28,000 rugs.\nDetails\nMeeting Point Bennahid #40 Derb Zaouiat Lhadar, Marrakesh 40030, open every day from 9:00 am to 7:00 pm, even during Ramadan\nEnding Point  Your purchase will be shipped to your home via DHL Express.\n\nAccessibility   Cushioned benches and chairs and piles of rugs available for sitting; salesman will bring everything to you\nWhat to bring    Dimensions and photos of the room(s) where you envision putting a Moroccan rug\nReviews\n4.8 stars (642 reviews)\nOn the reviews, tell Chat to make the math work with only 5 star and one star reviews\n\nMargo W April 2024 5 star \nMarrakech in my family room\nWow, I told the salesperson the size, color, style, and price I wanted. He returned with three rugs of the 28,000 in the store. All three fit the criteria. I wanted to buy two. I bought one. When I walk on it, it brings me back to Marrakech. \nRegina G five star\nHave Tea\nI didn\u2019t buy a rug, I have carpeting at home, but loved the hospitality. The way they pour the tea from several feet above the cup, amazing. After being lost in the Medina, it was nice to sit and relax.\n\nChad 1 star\nScam\nThe salesmen are inefficient. I didn\u2019t want a history lesson and don\u2019t care about the villagers who supposedly wove the rug by hand. I just wanted to know the price. I\u2019m sure the tour guide would have gotten a big kickback if I bought anything. I didn\u2019t. I didn\u2019t tip the guide either. I\u2019ll find something on eBay when I get home."
