    "verbatimText": "First line below the search box:\nGlobal / Travel / Things to Do When Your Retire / Semester Abroad\n\nStellenbosch Luxury Winelands Ebike Tour\n4 stars (1389 reviews) Free cancellation  R2295 \nDuration: 6 hours\nCancellation: Free up to 24 hours in advance\nMobile ticket: Yes\nLanguage: Afrikaans, English\nOverview\nIndulge in the ultimate luxury ebike tour in Stellenbosch, combining fine wines, stunning scenery, and first-class hospitality. Visit four historic wine estates, enjoy premium tastings, and relax over a leisurely lunch. This is the Wineland experience refined\u2014stylish, scenic, and effortlessly fun.\n\n\nWhy travelers book it:\n\t\u2022\tThey enjoyed a bike tour in Napa or Sonoma last year.\n\t\u2022\tThey want a respite from Africa.\n\t\u2022\tSouth African wines are excellent.\n\t\u2022\tThey already went on safari.\n\t\u2022\tThey have a free day before going on safari. \n\nGood to Know:\n\t\u2022\tApartheid ended thirty years ago.\n\t\u2022\tYou won\u2019t see any Black Africans in Stellenbosch.\n\t\u2022\tYour guide will be an Afrikaner.\n\t\u2022\tYou will think you are in California.\n\t\u2022\tOn the drive from Cape Town, you will pass miles and miles of corrugated tin shacks where too many Black South Africans still live in townships.\n\t\u2022\tYour Uber driver will be from Zimbabwe because, as bad as South Africa\u2019s economy is, Zimbabwe is worse.\n\nWhat\u2019s included\n\t\u2022\tFully guided tour (maximum 8 guests)\n\t\u2022\tElectric pedal assist mountain bike and helmet\n\t\u2022\tBottled water and snacks\n\t\u2022\tExclusive private vineyard access\n\t\u2022\tAll wine tastings and gourmet pairing experiences on route (4 estates visited)\n\t\u2022\tCheese, fruit, and charcuterie platter\n\t\u2022\tFirst-hand experience with South Africa\u2019s income inequality (the highest in the world)\nNot Included\n\t\u2022\tGratuities to Guides\n\t\u2022\tBottles of Wine purchased and shipped to your home country\n\t\u2022\tContact with Black South Africans\n\t\u2022\tInsight into the life of South Africans beyond the vineyards\n\t\u2022\tRationale for your guilt\nDetails\nMeeting Point: Skilpadvlei Wine Farm, Stellenbosch, 10:00 am\nEnd Point: Skilpadvlei Wine Farm, Stellenbosch, 4:00 pm\nAccessibility: Must be able to ride an ebike on dirt between rows of vines\nWhat to bring: Nothing needed\nRatings\n4 stars (1389 reviews) have chat divide, all excellent and terrible, nothing in the middle\nReviews:\nMargo W 5 stars March 2024\nCouldn\u2019t Get Past The Shacks\nTo be fair to the tour company, looking only at the tour itself: five stars. The tour provided exactly what it promised: a luxury experience, good ebikes, gorgeous scenery, excellent wines, and delicious cheese boards. But I could not shake the images of the miles of corrugated shacks we passed on the road to Stellenbosch. I couldn\u2019t get past the inequality. South Africa is amazing for tourists, not so much for its citizens. \nManagement reply: Margo, thank you for your positive review of our tour. We apologize for the poor people living on the road between Cape Town and our lovely town of Stellenbosch. We hope the wine helped erase the image. \n\nBill H 1 star, April 2025\nShould Have Taken A Van Tour\nToo much biking, not enough wine. No support vehicle, had to keep riding, and you had to pedal for the battery assist to work. Should have taken a wine tour in a van.\nManagement reply: Bill, we are sorry you did not expect to bike on our bike tour. In the future, we will clarify in our marketing materials that the Stellenbosch Luxury Winelands Ebike Tour is conducted on ebikes and we will repeat at least three times the information that you will ride 20 kilometers.\n\f"
